1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:01:00,000
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:01:02,942 --> 00:01:04,933
Who is it?

3
00:01:09,787 --> 00:01:12,089
Why is my manager here...

4
00:01:12,089 --> 00:01:14,287
Hello, I'm the owner of Unit 206.

5
00:01:14,287 --> 00:01:15,663
The owner?

6
00:01:15,663 --> 00:01:17,492
The owner?

7
00:01:17,492 --> 00:01:19,713
- Of this place?
- Yeah...

8
00:01:23,019 --> 00:01:25,285
Open the door.

9
00:01:32,972 --> 00:01:34,833
Please, just ten minutes.

10
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:37,560
No, five. Don't say anything.

11
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:40,501
- Okay?
- Hey, wait!

12
00:01:40,501 --> 00:01:42,988
What is she doing right now...

13
00:02:01,876 --> 00:02:03,965
Sir?

14
00:02:07,893 --> 00:02:10,163
Woo Hyun Jin?

15
00:02:10,163 --> 00:02:13,951
Oh, yes. You can come in.

16
00:02:18,810 --> 00:02:21,679
Woo Hyun Jin, why are you here...

17
00:02:22,272 --> 00:02:24,406
I know.

18
00:02:25,233 --> 00:02:26,981
So...

19
00:02:26,981 --> 00:02:29,070
You're...

20
00:02:29,070 --> 00:02:32,309
the owner here?

21
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:40,540
- Is that the guy?
- I looked like a total mess

22
00:02:40,540 --> 00:02:41,749
in front of him today.

23
00:02:41,749 --> 00:02:42,959
I know I looked awful.

24
00:02:42,959 --> 00:02:43,772
Yes, sir.

25
00:02:43,772 --> 00:02:45,079
He put his faith in me
and handed me this opportunity,

26
00:02:45,079 --> 00:02:46,552
so I need to pour everything I have into this

27
00:02:46,552 --> 00:02:48,678
and deliver real results.

28
00:02:48,678 --> 00:02:50,638
This isn't who I am.

29
00:02:50,638 --> 00:02:52,927
I really am Suzy to him...

30
00:02:52,927 --> 00:02:55,138
He was my first love.

31
00:02:55,138 --> 00:02:57,964
Do you know how much I liked him?

32
00:03:26,966 --> 00:03:28,968
What is this?

33
00:03:32,096 --> 00:03:34,682
Give me my bunny.

34
00:03:38,274 --> 00:03:40,307
My bunny!

35
00:03:41,164 --> 00:03:43,154
Hey, kid...

36
00:04:03,875 --> 00:04:05,633
Woo Hyun Jin.

37
00:04:05,633 --> 00:04:08,473
What is going on here?

38
00:04:09,216 --> 00:04:11,185
Let's step outside.

39
00:04:11,185 --> 00:04:13,734
We should talk out there.

40
00:04:17,887 --> 00:04:19,901
Let's go.

41
00:04:19,901 --> 00:04:21,641
Can you watch Woo Joo for a minute?

42
00:04:21,641 --> 00:04:23,807
You're okay with that, huh?

43
00:04:25,389 --> 00:04:28,087
This is so embarrassing.

44
00:04:39,163 --> 00:04:40,397
[Episode 5]
So... that's why

45
00:04:40,397 --> 00:04:44,039
I'm living here with him,
taking care of Woo Joo.

46
00:04:45,973 --> 00:04:48,226
That must've been hard.

47
00:04:49,756 --> 00:04:53,028
But I guess it's better than being alone.

48
00:04:53,028 --> 00:04:56,039
For Woo Joo and for me.

49
00:04:57,783 --> 00:05:01,264
Is there anything I can do to help?

50
00:05:01,264 --> 00:05:02,706
No.

51
00:05:02,706 --> 00:05:05,653
I'm okay. My in-law is here.

52
00:05:12,692 --> 00:05:14,110
First of all,

53
00:05:14,110 --> 00:05:16,115
you need to rest.

54
00:05:16,115 --> 00:05:17,948
It's been nonstop for you since yesterday.

55
00:05:17,948 --> 00:05:20,573
And this morning, I probably startled you too.

56
00:05:20,573 --> 00:05:22,121
Let's go.

57
00:05:22,121 --> 00:05:24,140
Yoon Seong...

58
00:05:25,705 --> 00:05:28,538
I'm sorry I lied.

59
00:05:29,802 --> 00:05:32,920
It wasn't easy to explain.

60
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:34,005
Still,

61
00:05:34,005 --> 00:05:36,549
I didn't have to lie about where I live.

62
00:05:36,549 --> 00:05:37,812
Yeah,

63
00:05:37,812 --> 00:05:40,458
that part did sting a little.

64
00:05:41,479 --> 00:05:43,756
It made me wonder if I've become someone

65
00:05:43,756 --> 00:05:46,618
you feel the need to hide things from.

66
00:06:12,801 --> 00:06:15,979
Hey, Tae Hyung.

67
00:06:24,059 --> 00:06:26,896
I'm sorry about earlier.

68
00:06:27,879 --> 00:06:29,165
Well...

69
00:06:29,165 --> 00:06:32,063
I was caught off guard too.

70
00:06:32,063 --> 00:06:34,143
That's why...

71
00:06:38,491 --> 00:06:41,369
Are you okay where you fell?

72
00:06:42,828 --> 00:06:45,665
It looks like you might bruise.

73
00:06:47,618 --> 00:06:49,084
Hey.

74
00:06:49,084 --> 00:06:50,628
I know you're upset,

75
00:06:50,628 --> 00:06:52,338
but when someone apologizes,
you could at least...

76
00:06:52,338 --> 00:06:53,506
Apologize?

77
00:06:53,506 --> 00:06:54,757
For what?

78
00:06:55,966 --> 00:06:57,839
For shoving me and the baby into a room

79
00:06:57,839 --> 00:06:59,437
like we were baggage

80
00:06:59,437 --> 00:07:01,144
when your first love showed up?

81
00:07:01,144 --> 00:07:02,736
Or...

82
00:07:03,945 --> 00:07:05,283
So you weren't busy working,

83
00:07:05,283 --> 00:07:07,536
you were busy rekindling things
with your first love

84
00:07:07,536 --> 00:07:09,104
to answer the phone when the kid got hurt?

85
00:07:09,104 --> 00:07:10,314
No.

86
00:07:10,314 --> 00:07:12,355
I told you earlier.

87
00:07:12,355 --> 00:07:14,021
I was really busy working.

88
00:07:14,021 --> 00:07:15,398
You sure?

89
00:07:15,398 --> 00:07:18,280
You couldn't even say a word in front of him.

90
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:20,024
Were you embarrassed to be raising a baby

91
00:07:20,024 --> 00:07:22,864
in front of your amazing first love?

92
00:07:22,864 --> 00:07:25,410
Don't talk like you know everything.

93
00:07:25,410 --> 00:07:27,118
I'm not embarrassed of Woo Joo at all.

94
00:07:27,118 --> 00:07:29,245
- Then were you embarrassed of me?
- Hey!

95
00:07:29,245 --> 00:07:31,289
Why are you twisting everything?

96
00:07:31,289 --> 00:07:33,255
What did I do?

97
00:07:38,717 --> 00:07:40,173
Forget it.

98
00:07:40,173 --> 00:07:43,236
Talking more won't change anything.

99
00:07:45,558 --> 00:07:48,060
Same here.

100
00:07:52,602 --> 00:07:54,187
What's his problem?

101
00:07:54,187 --> 00:07:57,207
Like my life isn't complicated enough.

102
00:08:00,906 --> 00:08:03,659
Beats me.

103
00:08:07,055 --> 00:08:09,681
This is so embarrassing.

104
00:08:16,779 --> 00:08:19,324
Do you know why he's so pissed?

105
00:08:19,324 --> 00:08:21,839
Maybe it's that woman he's living with.

106
00:08:21,839 --> 00:08:24,008
His moods have been all over the place lately.

107
00:08:24,008 --> 00:08:25,510
Isn't it because of her?

108
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:27,053
You mean... his in-law?

109
00:08:27,053 --> 00:08:29,013
I thought they were getting along fine.

110
00:08:29,013 --> 00:08:30,515
Fine? Not even close.

111
00:08:30,515 --> 00:08:32,391
When is that construction
even going to be done?

112
00:08:32,391 --> 00:08:36,484
Dragging the kid around everywhere
I go is exhausting.

113
00:08:43,699 --> 00:08:45,404
Living in that crappy place

114
00:08:45,404 --> 00:08:47,114
with that weird woman,

115
00:08:47,114 --> 00:08:50,039
I keep getting triggered over nothing.

116
00:08:50,039 --> 00:08:52,291
Triggered how, exactly?

117
00:08:52,291 --> 00:08:56,003
Don't even start. I had to meet her first love.

118
00:09:04,316 --> 00:09:07,382
[Photographer, Amy Choo]
You left without developing the photos.

119
00:09:09,553 --> 00:09:12,835
This is thin ice. Total thin ice.

120
00:09:13,937 --> 00:09:15,434
Tell me about it.

121
00:09:15,434 --> 00:09:16,894
We live in the same house.

122
00:09:16,894 --> 00:09:19,313
We can't keep it this awkward forever.

123
00:09:19,313 --> 00:09:22,321
We need to clear the air somehow.

124
00:09:22,321 --> 00:09:23,901
But Hyun Jin...

125
00:09:23,901 --> 00:09:25,212
You know what?

126
00:09:25,212 --> 00:09:28,786
I'm starting to
get suspicious of your roommate.

127
00:09:28,786 --> 00:09:30,383
- Why?
- Think about it.

128
00:09:30,383 --> 00:09:32,285
Sure, he could be annoyed you hid him.

129
00:09:32,285 --> 00:09:34,912
And he did trip and embarrass himself.

130
00:09:34,912 --> 00:09:37,652
But why was he that mad at you?

131
00:09:38,416 --> 00:09:39,834
What if...

132
00:09:39,834 --> 00:09:41,293
after that wild night,

133
00:09:41,293 --> 00:09:42,712
he started seeing you

134
00:09:42,712 --> 00:09:44,005
as a woman?

135
00:09:44,005 --> 00:09:46,007
Seriously, Se Yeon.

136
00:09:46,007 --> 00:09:47,846
Didn't I tell you to stop reading web novels?

137
00:09:47,846 --> 00:09:49,579
Your word choice is a little intense.

138
00:09:49,579 --> 00:09:52,468
And we are not like that.

139
00:10:13,956 --> 00:10:16,334
What are you doing here?

140
00:10:19,206 --> 00:10:22,126
I just got back from the archive.

141
00:10:22,126 --> 00:10:23,544
Let's head into the meeting.

142
00:10:23,544 --> 00:10:25,639
Okay.

143
00:10:28,759 --> 00:10:31,927
What you're looking at now
are GloMarket's key needs.

144
00:10:31,927 --> 00:10:33,763
They want stronger storytelling

145
00:10:33,763 --> 00:10:36,974
for each individual product.

146
00:10:36,974 --> 00:10:38,605
So we'll be handling visual directing

147
00:10:38,605 --> 00:10:40,978
with an external specialist team.

148
00:10:40,978 --> 00:10:42,313
Sir,

149
00:10:42,313 --> 00:10:45,274
the shortlist is already finalized, right?

150
00:10:45,274 --> 00:10:47,468
We've already reached out and sent proposals.

151
00:10:47,468 --> 00:10:50,134
I'll share updates once it's confirmed.

152
00:10:54,314 --> 00:10:56,487
Woo Hyun Jin.

153
00:10:58,207 --> 00:10:59,288
I'd like you

154
00:10:59,288 --> 00:11:02,280
to take on the storytelling strategy.

155
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:03,786
Your narrative approach to K-food

156
00:11:03,786 --> 00:11:06,659
in the GloMarket proposal worked well.

157
00:11:06,659 --> 00:11:08,497
Put together a proposal with the concept

158
00:11:08,497 --> 00:11:11,023
and a structured story outline attached.

159
00:11:11,926 --> 00:11:14,970
Yes, got it.

160
00:11:14,970 --> 00:11:17,113
You can head out now.

161
00:11:18,432 --> 00:11:20,476
Okay, then...

162
00:11:34,573 --> 00:11:36,455
I'm honestly speechless right now.

163
00:11:36,455 --> 00:11:38,064
Is it true that our great Amy Choo

164
00:11:38,064 --> 00:11:39,917
mentioned Sun Tae Hyung in the interview?

165
00:11:39,917 --> 00:11:43,629
You know I hate stopping
in the middle of work. Right?

166
00:11:43,629 --> 00:11:45,000
Eat while you listen.

167
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,340
Have you ever once mentioned my name

168
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:48,759
while working with me?

169
00:11:48,759 --> 00:11:51,216
Jo Moo Saeng.

170
00:11:51,216 --> 00:11:53,531
Congratulations on your retirement.

171
00:11:53,531 --> 00:11:56,470
You're finally free from me.

172
00:11:56,470 --> 00:11:59,276
I'm passing Sun Tae Hyung.

173
00:11:59,276 --> 00:12:01,729
What, not happy?

174
00:12:03,060 --> 00:12:04,770
No, I'm so happy.

175
00:12:04,770 --> 00:12:06,605
So where should I travel next?

176
00:12:06,605 --> 00:12:08,695
Book your ticket for a month from now.

177
00:12:08,695 --> 00:12:11,616
Wrap up your handover properly.

178
00:12:12,584 --> 00:12:15,077
And you still haven't signed
the divorce papers.

179
00:12:15,077 --> 00:12:16,574
Why not?

180
00:12:16,574 --> 00:12:19,762
After twenty years of putting up with you,

181
00:12:19,762 --> 00:12:21,746
you think I'd sign those terms?

182
00:12:21,746 --> 00:12:23,205
I want alimony.

183
00:12:23,205 --> 00:12:26,046
And my share of the assets. The house too.

184
00:12:26,046 --> 00:12:28,043
Then book your ticket a year from now.

185
00:12:28,043 --> 00:12:30,809
This lawsuit's going to drag on.

186
00:12:38,709 --> 00:12:41,148
What about Kkotnim?

187
00:12:41,148 --> 00:12:44,462
Don't even think about seeing her.

188
00:12:47,354 --> 00:12:48,397
Fine. I won't.

189
00:12:48,397 --> 00:12:50,736
Just sign the papers.

190
00:12:51,465 --> 00:12:53,390
Come in.

191
00:13:04,705 --> 00:13:06,835
You didn't bring the baby today?

192
00:13:06,835 --> 00:13:09,418
I left the baby with a friend for a bit.

193
00:13:09,418 --> 00:13:11,879
You've got some nerve.

194
00:13:11,879 --> 00:13:13,760
Leaving your film and camera behind.

195
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:16,472
Were you expecting me to develop it?

196
00:13:17,508 --> 00:13:18,515
I'm sorry.

197
00:13:18,515 --> 00:13:20,292
I already looked at them.

198
00:13:20,292 --> 00:13:24,098
You don't think
this is a baby photo studio, do you?

199
00:13:29,943 --> 00:13:32,321
Hey, kid.

200
00:13:34,793 --> 00:13:37,907
You got picked because of this.

201
00:13:37,907 --> 00:13:40,324
Especially this shot.

202
00:13:42,228 --> 00:13:44,273
There's heart in it.

203
00:13:44,273 --> 00:13:46,244
Working with film gives you space. Right?

204
00:13:46,244 --> 00:13:49,604
You wait for it.
You imagine what it'll look like.

205
00:13:49,604 --> 00:13:51,340
That's what makes it fun.

206
00:13:51,340 --> 00:13:54,343
Your shots were interesting too.

207
00:13:55,677 --> 00:13:59,134
I'm not good at waiting.

208
00:13:59,134 --> 00:14:01,099
That's why I don't really work with film.

209
00:14:01,099 --> 00:14:03,394
It's not my thing.

210
00:14:04,102 --> 00:14:06,149
Yeah?

211
00:14:06,149 --> 00:14:08,120
Then what's this?

212
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:14,467
- Your wife?
- Huh?

213
00:14:14,467 --> 00:14:16,485
- Or your girlfriend?
- No. Never.

214
00:14:16,485 --> 00:14:19,113
They say strong denial means it's true.

215
00:14:19,113 --> 00:14:22,575
Mine's genuinely a "no."

216
00:14:22,575 --> 00:14:24,456
Anyway.

217
00:14:24,456 --> 00:14:27,526
Here's a proposal that came in.

218
00:14:27,526 --> 00:14:29,623
Take a look at your next project.

219
00:14:29,623 --> 00:14:32,543
Put that same heart into it.

220
00:14:32,543 --> 00:14:34,503
Because this first project

221
00:14:34,503 --> 00:14:37,202
is going to be your salary.

222
00:14:53,647 --> 00:14:56,032
But the lens doesn't lie.

223
00:14:56,972 --> 00:14:58,527
The way you look at someone.

224
00:14:58,527 --> 00:15:00,597
The heart you put into the shot.

225
00:15:00,597 --> 00:15:03,346
You don't get moments like that
without affection.

226
00:15:03,346 --> 00:15:06,626
In the end, the camera reflects your heart.

227
00:15:06,626 --> 00:15:07,870
No.

228
00:15:07,870 --> 00:15:09,733
"Affection?" Not even close.

229
00:15:09,733 --> 00:15:11,128
Let's go, kid.

230
00:15:11,128 --> 00:15:14,471
I need to make things right with your aunt.

231
00:15:14,471 --> 00:15:16,819
Got any bright ideas?

232
00:15:19,219 --> 00:15:22,890
And how am I supposed to fix things with him?

233
00:15:24,013 --> 00:15:26,523
I should apologize first, right?

234
00:15:27,262 --> 00:15:29,342
Hyun Jin?

235
00:15:30,752 --> 00:15:32,583
Hello.

236
00:15:32,583 --> 00:15:34,303
Just a second...

237
00:15:34,303 --> 00:15:35,461
Good to see you here.

238
00:15:35,461 --> 00:15:37,464
I was meaning to talk to you.

239
00:15:37,464 --> 00:15:39,526
Want to go camping tomorrow?

240
00:15:39,526 --> 00:15:40,569
Camping?

241
00:15:40,569 --> 00:15:41,773
The weather's nice.

242
00:15:41,773 --> 00:15:43,240
We could let the kids run around.

243
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:45,583
It'd be a good change of pace.

244
00:15:45,583 --> 00:15:48,160
Right now, it seems...

245
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:51,156
more psychological than physical.

246
00:15:59,009 --> 00:16:01,512
Oh, are you packing?

247
00:16:02,554 --> 00:16:05,307
Got the bug spray...

248
00:16:05,307 --> 00:16:07,846
Are they planning to play in the water?

249
00:16:07,846 --> 00:16:09,550
Should we pack an extra outfit for you?

250
00:16:11,910 --> 00:16:13,852
Just in case,

251
00:16:13,852 --> 00:16:16,412
we should bring everything.

252
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:47,526
Hey... well...

253
00:16:55,144 --> 00:16:57,130
What is it?

254
00:16:57,776 --> 00:17:01,197
Would you like to come camping with us?

255
00:17:02,609 --> 00:17:03,865
All of a sudden?

256
00:17:03,865 --> 00:17:06,113
It's such a nice day.

257
00:17:06,113 --> 00:17:09,521
I thought it'd be nice to take Woo Joo out.

258
00:17:09,521 --> 00:17:11,466
And you remember...

259
00:17:11,466 --> 00:17:12,651
they said Woo Joo needs

260
00:17:12,651 --> 00:17:14,747
attentive care from his guardians, right?

261
00:17:14,747 --> 00:17:16,294
This is part of that.

262
00:17:16,294 --> 00:17:18,756
Well... okay.

263
00:17:19,619 --> 00:17:20,632
Oh, really?

264
00:17:20,632 --> 00:17:22,651
I told you I'm going. You don't trust me?

265
00:17:22,651 --> 00:17:24,841
There you go again, talking like that.

266
00:17:24,841 --> 00:17:27,468
Everything else is perfectly set up,

267
00:17:27,468 --> 00:17:30,429
so we just show up and relax.

268
00:17:30,429 --> 00:17:32,608
Wait, it's not just the three of us?

269
00:17:32,608 --> 00:17:34,925
Stop it! Where's my jelly?

270
00:17:34,925 --> 00:17:36,018
Daddy!

271
00:17:36,018 --> 00:17:37,061
Mommy!

272
00:17:37,061 --> 00:17:39,563
Lee Bom keeps throwing snacks at me!

273
00:17:39,563 --> 00:17:42,316
Lee Bom,
I told you not to pick on your brother.

274
00:17:42,316 --> 00:17:45,482
Mommy, Lee Yeo Reum ate all my jelly!

275
00:17:45,482 --> 00:17:47,362
I didn't!

276
00:17:47,362 --> 00:17:49,278
Actually... I'm the one eating it.

277
00:17:49,278 --> 00:17:50,991
Daddy!

278
00:17:50,991 --> 00:17:52,394
Hey! Don't throw that!

279
00:17:52,394 --> 00:17:54,119
Come on...

280
00:17:54,119 --> 00:17:55,287
Knock it off!

281
00:17:55,287 --> 00:17:58,628
You didn't say there would be this many kids.

282
00:17:58,628 --> 00:18:02,544
It'll feel totally relaxing once we get there.

283
00:18:02,544 --> 00:18:03,670
Stop it!

284
00:18:03,670 --> 00:18:04,880
I said stop!

285
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:07,348
You stop!

286
00:18:13,341 --> 00:18:16,141
This is going to take forever.
Just give it to me.

287
00:18:16,141 --> 00:18:19,361
Oh, you know how to set up a tent?

288
00:18:19,949 --> 00:18:22,435
Want me to show you how it's done?

289
00:18:47,939 --> 00:18:50,499
Pull that a little.

290
00:18:54,684 --> 00:18:57,103
You said you were good at this.

291
00:18:57,103 --> 00:18:59,898
Didn't you say you could set up
a 24-man military tent in five minutes?

292
00:18:59,898 --> 00:19:01,779
This is...

293
00:19:01,779 --> 00:19:04,110
Something's seriously wrong with it.

294
00:19:04,110 --> 00:19:05,534
The slots don't even line up.

295
00:19:05,534 --> 00:19:08,156
This thing's defective.

296
00:19:08,156 --> 00:19:09,638
Need some help?

297
00:19:09,638 --> 00:19:11,080
Really?

298
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:13,286
No, we've got it. It's basically done.

299
00:19:13,286 --> 00:19:16,124
Just go play with your kids.

300
00:19:26,007 --> 00:19:27,050
Finally... done.

301
00:19:27,050 --> 00:19:28,696
See? No big deal.

302
00:19:28,696 --> 00:19:30,095
Tent attack!

303
00:19:30,095 --> 00:19:32,232
Nice try, kid.

304
00:19:32,232 --> 00:19:34,112
Nice!

305
00:19:41,232 --> 00:19:43,265
Run!

306
00:19:46,253 --> 00:19:48,137
Oh, my back...

307
00:19:50,493 --> 00:19:53,053
Story of my life.

308
00:19:53,053 --> 00:19:55,353
Good work.

309
00:19:58,319 --> 00:20:00,710
I realized something.

310
00:20:00,710 --> 00:20:03,098
What?

311
00:20:03,098 --> 00:20:05,545
I hate camping.

312
00:20:06,635 --> 00:20:08,248
Still,

313
00:20:08,248 --> 00:20:11,235
I think we achieved our goal.

314
00:20:23,067 --> 00:20:25,008
Woo Joo!

315
00:20:25,972 --> 00:20:28,232
Come here. Let's play.

316
00:20:31,594 --> 00:20:33,852
He does look happy.

317
00:20:33,852 --> 00:20:35,795
Woo Joo.

318
00:20:48,777 --> 00:20:50,661
- Hey...
- Uh...

319
00:20:57,342 --> 00:20:59,074
You

320
00:20:59,074 --> 00:21:01,115
go first.

321
00:21:02,201 --> 00:21:04,294
You know...

322
00:21:13,345 --> 00:21:14,746
About yesterday, I was a little...

323
00:21:14,746 --> 00:21:17,339
Hyun Jin! I think Woo Joo pooped.

324
00:21:17,339 --> 00:21:19,393
Okay, hold on.

325
00:21:19,393 --> 00:21:21,445
Just a second.

326
00:21:23,378 --> 00:21:24,807
Woo Joo, did you pee?

327
00:21:24,807 --> 00:21:27,698
Great timing.

328
00:21:32,879 --> 00:21:33,919
Excuse me, Mr. Sun.

329
00:21:33,919 --> 00:21:35,661
Could you take a picture of me?

330
00:21:35,661 --> 00:21:38,298
So I can send it to my boyfriend.

331
00:21:43,250 --> 00:21:47,323
You already have a boyfriend at your age?

332
00:21:49,864 --> 00:21:51,718
Come here. I will take it.

333
00:21:51,718 --> 00:21:53,530
By the way, I am not a mister.
I am a young uncle.

334
00:21:53,530 --> 00:21:55,366
Let's go.

335
00:22:01,583 --> 00:22:03,384
That's it.

336
00:22:09,992 --> 00:22:11,226
- Wow.
- Two.

337
00:22:11,226 --> 00:22:12,392
You have two?

338
00:22:12,392 --> 00:22:13,772
One, two.

339
00:22:13,772 --> 00:22:15,899
- Peace.
- Peace.

340
00:22:15,899 --> 00:22:17,568
Do a peace sign.

341
00:22:17,568 --> 00:22:19,804
I don't want to.

342
00:22:20,490 --> 00:22:22,876
I'm recording a video right now.

343
00:22:27,713 --> 00:22:29,756
Peace!

344
00:22:29,756 --> 00:22:32,214
That's so fast.

345
00:22:38,114 --> 00:22:39,974
So tired.

346
00:22:42,317 --> 00:22:44,219
These kids never get tired.

347
00:22:44,219 --> 00:22:46,552
What are they, wild animals?

348
00:23:02,368 --> 00:23:05,662
[Manager Park Yoon Seong]

349
00:23:08,813 --> 00:23:10,946
You two are in-laws?

350
00:23:10,946 --> 00:23:15,361
I thought you were either dating or cousins.

351
00:23:15,361 --> 00:23:16,920
In-laws never crossed my mind.

352
00:23:16,920 --> 00:23:19,657
Dating? Please. No way.

353
00:23:19,657 --> 00:23:22,371
Absolutely not.

354
00:23:22,371 --> 00:23:25,689
In-laws are not really family, right?

355
00:23:25,689 --> 00:23:27,017
That is kind of awkward.

356
00:23:27,017 --> 00:23:28,968
Was it not uncomfortable?

357
00:23:28,968 --> 00:23:30,755
It was.

358
00:23:30,755 --> 00:23:32,332
Honestly,

359
00:23:32,332 --> 00:23:35,978
there are a lot of things we do not agree on.

360
00:23:35,978 --> 00:23:37,312
But what can I do?

361
00:23:37,312 --> 00:23:39,208
We are not really family anyway.

362
00:23:39,208 --> 00:23:42,594
And he is moving out soon.

363
00:23:43,234 --> 00:23:46,100
I will be raising Woo Joo on my own.

364
00:23:55,745 --> 00:23:56,959
Alright, let us eat.

365
00:23:56,959 --> 00:23:58,418
Who wants meat?

366
00:23:58,418 --> 00:23:59,503
Me.

367
00:23:59,503 --> 00:24:00,614
Yeah?

368
00:24:00,614 --> 00:24:02,654
This turned out great.

369
00:24:02,654 --> 00:24:04,287
It smells so good.

370
00:24:04,287 --> 00:24:06,400
Eat up.

371
00:24:07,978 --> 00:24:09,145
Say "thank you" for him.

372
00:24:09,145 --> 00:24:11,862
- Thank you, Dad.
- Thank you, Dad.

373
00:24:11,862 --> 00:24:14,276
Sausage.

374
00:24:14,276 --> 00:24:15,302
You are eating well.

375
00:24:15,302 --> 00:24:16,877
It is delicious.

376
00:24:16,877 --> 00:24:19,090
Is it?

377
00:24:22,084 --> 00:24:23,912
Woo Joo's uncle is not eating.

378
00:24:23,912 --> 00:24:26,229
I checked the tent earlier. He was not there.

379
00:24:26,229 --> 00:24:27,885
Where did he go?

380
00:24:27,885 --> 00:24:29,962
Go ahead and eat.

381
00:24:30,659 --> 00:24:32,564
Where did Uncle go?

382
00:24:32,564 --> 00:24:33,935
Tae Hyung!

383
00:24:33,935 --> 00:24:35,904
Tae Hyung!

384
00:24:40,521 --> 00:24:42,589
Did he not hear me?

385
00:24:43,521 --> 00:24:45,614
Tae Hyung!

386
00:24:46,740 --> 00:24:47,850
Hey.

387
00:24:47,850 --> 00:24:49,547
Are you feeling sick?

388
00:24:49,547 --> 00:24:51,571
No.

389
00:24:51,571 --> 00:24:52,810
Then...

390
00:24:52,810 --> 00:24:55,246
Is something wrong?

391
00:24:55,246 --> 00:24:57,111
No.

392
00:24:57,983 --> 00:25:00,043
You are not eating? It is really good.

393
00:25:00,043 --> 00:25:01,818
No, thank you. I am fine.

394
00:25:01,818 --> 00:25:03,136
Why not?

395
00:25:03,136 --> 00:25:04,636
Just eat. Do not worry about me.

396
00:25:04,636 --> 00:25:07,516
Come on, just one bite.

397
00:25:07,516 --> 00:25:08,558
It is Iberico pork neck.

398
00:25:08,558 --> 00:25:11,479
- Just try one bite.
- I said I am fine.

399
00:25:13,041 --> 00:25:15,714
Why are you acting like this?

400
00:25:19,482 --> 00:25:21,565
- I said I am not eating.
- I am sorry.

401
00:25:21,565 --> 00:25:24,242
I guess I was bothering you.

402
00:25:27,927 --> 00:25:31,372
Look, that uncle is such a piece of work.

403
00:25:31,372 --> 00:25:34,001
Lee Bom, use kind words.

404
00:25:35,490 --> 00:25:37,318
- Why?
- Watch your language.

405
00:25:37,318 --> 00:25:40,179
She picked that up from you.

406
00:25:53,089 --> 00:25:56,235
Seriously, what is wrong with him?

407
00:25:56,235 --> 00:25:58,276
Such a waste of good meat.

408
00:25:58,276 --> 00:26:00,151
We came all the way here to get along.

409
00:26:00,151 --> 00:26:02,572
Why is he acting like that?

410
00:26:07,380 --> 00:26:09,485
- Hello?
- It is me.

411
00:26:09,485 --> 00:26:12,764
I texted you, but you didn't reply, so...

412
00:26:12,764 --> 00:26:15,617
I'm sorry. I didn't see it.

413
00:26:15,617 --> 00:26:16,709
Is something wrong?

414
00:26:16,709 --> 00:26:17,919
GloMarket says

415
00:26:17,919 --> 00:26:19,993
they sent over the local food safety standards,

416
00:26:19,993 --> 00:26:21,954
but I think they sent it to your email,
not mine.

417
00:26:21,954 --> 00:26:22,965
Can you forward it to me?

418
00:26:22,965 --> 00:26:24,945
Sure, just a second.

419
00:26:24,945 --> 00:26:27,212
[Manager Park Yoon Seong]

420
00:26:30,165 --> 00:26:32,164
Oh, you must be out right now.

421
00:26:32,164 --> 00:26:34,563
Sorry.

422
00:26:34,563 --> 00:26:35,603
It's okay.

423
00:26:35,603 --> 00:26:38,733
I'm camping with Woo Joo.

424
00:26:39,907 --> 00:26:41,010
I just sent it.

425
00:26:41,010 --> 00:26:43,039
Okay, thanks.

426
00:26:43,039 --> 00:26:44,644
By the way,

427
00:26:44,644 --> 00:26:48,196
they also sent
the projected strategy plan by country.

428
00:26:48,196 --> 00:26:49,935
Did you get that?

429
00:26:49,935 --> 00:26:51,005
What?

430
00:26:51,005 --> 00:26:52,287
I couldn't hear you.

431
00:26:52,287 --> 00:26:54,376
Hold on.

432
00:26:59,337 --> 00:27:02,412
[Off Limits]

433
00:27:06,660 --> 00:27:08,914
- Why isn't Hyun Jin back yet?
- Are you not eating?

434
00:27:08,914 --> 00:27:10,247
Here.

435
00:27:10,247 --> 00:27:11,958
Excuse me, Woo Joo's uncle.

436
00:27:11,958 --> 00:27:14,472
Is it going to take her much longer?

437
00:27:14,472 --> 00:27:16,732
It is already dark.

438
00:27:17,331 --> 00:27:19,941
I am not sure.

439
00:27:19,941 --> 00:27:22,069
Why don't you try calling her?

440
00:27:22,069 --> 00:27:25,556
I did. Her phone is completely off.

441
00:27:26,519 --> 00:27:29,159
And honestly, were you not a bit harsh?

442
00:27:29,159 --> 00:27:31,881
Hyun Jin thinks very highly of you.

443
00:27:31,881 --> 00:27:33,648
I already heard...

444
00:27:33,648 --> 00:27:36,063
Huh? Heard what?

445
00:27:36,063 --> 00:27:37,929
She feels really sad

446
00:27:37,929 --> 00:27:40,449
about you moving out.

447
00:27:41,519 --> 00:27:43,690
And he is moving out soon.

448
00:27:43,690 --> 00:27:45,726
So...

449
00:27:47,390 --> 00:27:49,617
I am sad.

450
00:27:50,374 --> 00:27:53,317
At first, it felt awkward.

451
00:27:53,317 --> 00:27:56,758
I honestly doubted
we could ever live under the same roof...

452
00:27:57,424 --> 00:27:59,123
But now...

453
00:27:59,123 --> 00:28:01,437
I'm going to miss him.

454
00:28:03,088 --> 00:28:06,184
Once he leaves,

455
00:28:06,184 --> 00:28:08,483
it feels like he will never see Woo Joo again,

456
00:28:08,483 --> 00:28:10,856
or me.

457
00:28:13,650 --> 00:28:15,950
Still, he is a good person.

458
00:28:15,950 --> 00:28:17,094
Well,

459
00:28:17,094 --> 00:28:19,690
he complains sometimes, but...

460
00:28:20,442 --> 00:28:23,292
I get him now.

461
00:28:23,292 --> 00:28:25,505
She said you are just not great with words,

462
00:28:25,505 --> 00:28:27,066
but you are better than you seem.

463
00:28:27,066 --> 00:28:29,092
She also said you are really warm with Woo Joo.

464
00:28:29,092 --> 00:28:31,427
She was praising you like that,
and you throw a plate?

465
00:28:31,427 --> 00:28:33,714
That was too much.

466
00:28:36,098 --> 00:28:37,670
Could you watch the baby for a moment?

467
00:28:37,670 --> 00:28:39,736
And please keep trying to call Hyun Jin.

468
00:28:39,736 --> 00:28:41,630
Thank you.

469
00:28:43,057 --> 00:28:45,275
Finally... you get it.

470
00:28:58,188 --> 00:29:00,174
Hyun Jin!

471
00:29:03,638 --> 00:29:06,751
Shouldn't we call the police?

472
00:29:07,457 --> 00:29:09,925
Okay, please.

473
00:29:09,925 --> 00:29:11,410
Where did she go?

474
00:29:11,410 --> 00:29:13,317
Hyun Jin!

475
00:29:14,595 --> 00:29:16,036
Excuse me, have you seen a woman...

476
00:29:16,036 --> 00:29:18,117
about this tall,
gray sweatpants and a blue jacket...

477
00:29:18,117 --> 00:29:19,556
No, I haven't seen her.

478
00:29:19,556 --> 00:29:21,915
Sorry.

479
00:29:21,915 --> 00:29:23,903
Hyun Jin!

480
00:29:27,339 --> 00:29:30,015
Woo Hyun Jin!

481
00:29:30,015 --> 00:29:31,825
Please...

482
00:29:31,825 --> 00:29:34,075
Woo Hyun Jin!

483
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:40,833
Woo Hyun Jin!

484
00:29:40,833 --> 00:29:42,778
Tae Hyung!

485
00:29:42,778 --> 00:29:45,296
- Tae Hyung!
- Hey...

486
00:29:45,296 --> 00:29:47,989
- It's you, right?
- Hyun Jin!

487
00:30:07,134 --> 00:30:09,179
Hyun Jin...

488
00:30:13,731 --> 00:30:16,156
This is driving me crazy.

489
00:30:16,156 --> 00:30:17,923
Tae Hyung...

490
00:30:17,923 --> 00:30:19,430
Why did you come all the way out here?

491
00:30:19,430 --> 00:30:21,718
I thought that path earlier...

492
00:30:21,718 --> 00:30:23,955
people were walking back and forth,

493
00:30:23,955 --> 00:30:26,306
so I assumed it was a trail...

494
00:30:26,306 --> 00:30:28,443
- But it kept getting stranger and stranger...
- What are you even saying?

495
00:30:28,443 --> 00:30:30,989
I don't even know where I am...

496
00:30:30,989 --> 00:30:33,563
Just wait there. I'm coming to you.

497
00:30:43,881 --> 00:30:46,181
Stand up first.

498
00:30:47,424 --> 00:30:50,741
Are you hurt? Did you twist your ankle?

499
00:30:50,741 --> 00:30:52,764
Hold this.

500
00:30:55,659 --> 00:30:57,572
Be careful.

501
00:31:02,947 --> 00:31:04,015
Be careful.

502
00:31:04,015 --> 00:31:06,001
It's slippery.

503
00:31:07,006 --> 00:31:09,274
Yes, I found her.

504
00:31:09,274 --> 00:31:12,293
Woo Joo's doing okay, right?

505
00:31:12,895 --> 00:31:14,927
Okay.

506
00:31:24,523 --> 00:31:25,632
I'm fine.

507
00:31:25,632 --> 00:31:27,379
No, hurry.

508
00:31:27,379 --> 00:31:29,107
We need to check it.

509
00:31:29,107 --> 00:31:32,658
If the blood dries,
it'll stick to your clothes.

510
00:31:40,941 --> 00:31:43,728
It's all scraped up.

511
00:31:47,982 --> 00:31:49,921
Does it hurt?

512
00:32:12,501 --> 00:32:14,807
We should go to a hospital first.

513
00:32:28,360 --> 00:32:30,701
Thank you.

514
00:32:30,701 --> 00:32:33,594
For coming to find me.

515
00:32:33,594 --> 00:32:37,407
I was really scared back there.

516
00:32:39,227 --> 00:32:40,634
But when I heard your voice,

517
00:32:40,634 --> 00:32:42,805
I felt relieved.

518
00:32:46,768 --> 00:32:48,635
I guess...

519
00:32:50,402 --> 00:32:53,705
I rely on you more than I thought.

520
00:32:56,275 --> 00:32:57,861
Well,

521
00:32:57,861 --> 00:33:01,040
if you're stranded alone in the woods,

522
00:33:01,040 --> 00:33:03,647
you'd feel relieved
seeing even your worst enemy.

523
00:33:03,647 --> 00:33:05,022
Come on.

524
00:33:05,022 --> 00:33:06,827
When someone says thank you, just take it.

525
00:33:06,827 --> 00:33:09,665
That emotional moment lasted,
what, thirty seconds?

526
00:33:16,288 --> 00:33:18,148
You...

527
00:33:18,148 --> 00:33:20,880
You hate rainy days, right?

528
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:23,261
You're completely soaked.

529
00:33:23,261 --> 00:33:25,104
It's not...

530
00:33:25,965 --> 00:33:29,458
It's not that I hate getting wet.

531
00:33:29,458 --> 00:33:32,351
Then why do you hate them?

532
00:33:36,060 --> 00:33:38,559
For the opposite reason you do.

533
00:33:41,573 --> 00:33:44,114
You said you liked rainy days

534
00:33:44,852 --> 00:33:47,453
because your sister would always come get you.

535
00:33:47,453 --> 00:33:49,286
Right?

536
00:33:53,466 --> 00:33:55,807
For me, when it rained...

537
00:33:56,976 --> 00:34:00,276
I remember waiting for someone
for a very long time.

538
00:34:09,310 --> 00:34:12,123
I remember expecting that person to come.

539
00:34:13,647 --> 00:34:16,054
But that expectation

540
00:34:17,373 --> 00:34:19,646
was never met. Not even once.

541
00:34:21,515 --> 00:34:24,061
That's why I hate rainy days.

542
00:34:32,624 --> 00:34:36,919
You knew that was about Sun Woo Jin,
the one you care so much about. Right?

543
00:34:38,169 --> 00:34:40,548
He's not even that good of a brother.

544
00:34:45,426 --> 00:34:48,012
Well, we should head back.

545
00:34:48,012 --> 00:34:50,433
Looks like the rain's stopped.

546
00:34:53,590 --> 00:34:56,177
I'll come get you.

547
00:35:01,513 --> 00:35:03,836
Well...

548
00:35:03,836 --> 00:35:05,988
I can't promise every time,

549
00:35:05,988 --> 00:35:07,821
but sometimes...

550
00:35:09,325 --> 00:35:12,413
sometimes I'll come meet you.

551
00:35:13,095 --> 00:35:14,955
So if there's a day

552
00:35:14,955 --> 00:35:18,748
when you're stuck in the rain
without an umbrella,

553
00:35:18,748 --> 00:35:21,697
just call me.

554
00:35:21,697 --> 00:35:24,477
I'll be your umbrella.

555
00:35:46,252 --> 00:35:47,363
Hey...

556
00:35:47,363 --> 00:35:48,489
Tae Hyung.

557
00:35:48,489 --> 00:35:50,729
Do not ask if you're heavy.

558
00:35:50,729 --> 00:35:52,525
It is cliché.

559
00:35:52,525 --> 00:35:53,914
And you should gain some weight.

560
00:35:53,914 --> 00:35:56,367
You might blow away in the wind.

561
00:35:58,655 --> 00:36:01,126
Do not swing your legs.

562
00:36:01,126 --> 00:36:02,211
It is dangerous.

563
00:36:02,211 --> 00:36:04,298
I might drop you.

564
00:36:08,665 --> 00:36:10,804
So...

565
00:36:10,804 --> 00:36:13,168
Are we friends now?

566
00:36:14,843 --> 00:36:16,203
Friends?

567
00:36:16,203 --> 00:36:18,823
You know, we are the same age.

568
00:36:18,823 --> 00:36:20,368
When people fight and make up,

569
00:36:20,368 --> 00:36:22,583
do they not usually become friends?

570
00:36:22,583 --> 00:36:24,498
What do you think?

571
00:36:24,498 --> 00:36:25,914
No thanks.

572
00:36:25,914 --> 00:36:27,944
Why not?

573
00:36:31,354 --> 00:36:32,575
Oh, right.

574
00:36:32,575 --> 00:36:34,543
We are a little closer than friends.

575
00:36:34,543 --> 00:36:36,157
Family?

576
00:36:36,157 --> 00:36:38,436
I don't like that either.

577
00:36:39,759 --> 00:36:42,305
Forget it. Put me down.

578
00:36:42,305 --> 00:36:44,485
If we are not friends, why are you carrying me?

579
00:36:44,485 --> 00:36:46,818
Stay still. It is dangerous.

580
00:36:46,818 --> 00:36:49,341
No, just put me down!

581
00:36:49,341 --> 00:36:50,537
Fine.

582
00:36:50,537 --> 00:36:52,583
Okay. Friends.

583
00:36:53,251 --> 00:36:54,531
Really?

584
00:36:54,531 --> 00:36:56,791
Alright, Sun Tae Hyung.

585
00:36:57,553 --> 00:37:00,319
Let us drop the formalities too.

586
00:37:00,319 --> 00:37:02,870
Do whatever you want, Woo Hyun Jin.

587
00:37:05,484 --> 00:37:08,401
Make sure you eat properly.

588
00:37:09,160 --> 00:37:11,128
Okay.

589
00:37:12,002 --> 00:37:13,585
I wonder what Woo Joo is doing.

590
00:37:13,585 --> 00:37:15,141
I miss him.

591
00:37:15,141 --> 00:37:17,781
He is probably having fun.

592
00:37:17,781 --> 00:37:19,873
He is a bright kid. He will be fine anywhere.

593
00:37:19,873 --> 00:37:22,101
Woo Joo!

594
00:37:22,101 --> 00:37:25,094
Hyun Jin, are you okay?

595
00:37:25,094 --> 00:37:27,565
Yes. I am sorry for worrying you.

596
00:37:27,565 --> 00:37:30,211
Given how we look,

597
00:37:30,211 --> 00:37:33,064
I think we should head home.

598
00:37:35,282 --> 00:37:37,973
He passed out after drinking beer.

599
00:37:37,973 --> 00:37:40,308
Don't worry about us. We're really fine.

600
00:37:40,308 --> 00:37:42,047
How are you getting back at this hour?

601
00:37:42,047 --> 00:37:44,221
I called a taxi. You do not have to see us off.

602
00:37:44,221 --> 00:37:46,365
We had a great time today.

603
00:37:46,365 --> 00:37:47,659
Thank you.

604
00:37:47,659 --> 00:37:50,832
- Get home safe.
- Thank you.

605
00:37:56,139 --> 00:37:57,203
Hey, kid.

606
00:37:57,203 --> 00:37:59,182
Did you have fun today?

607
00:37:59,182 --> 00:38:00,654
Yeah.

608
00:38:00,654 --> 00:38:02,474
Look.

609
00:38:03,274 --> 00:38:05,300
What is that?

610
00:38:05,300 --> 00:38:06,700
You know what?

611
00:38:06,700 --> 00:38:09,260
A robot pops out from there.

612
00:38:10,097 --> 00:38:12,004
What do you think?

613
00:38:25,066 --> 00:38:27,983
Pat Bunny gently, like this.

614
00:38:27,983 --> 00:38:29,645
Tell him to go night-night.

615
00:38:29,645 --> 00:38:31,404
Isn't the night view pretty?

616
00:38:31,404 --> 00:38:33,477
- Pretty?
- Yeah.

617
00:38:36,745 --> 00:38:39,050
- Are you not sleepy?
- No.

618
00:38:43,501 --> 00:38:46,195
Wouldn't it be better if you rode on my back?

619
00:38:46,195 --> 00:38:47,662
Or should we go to the hospital?

620
00:38:47,662 --> 00:38:49,862
If we go now, it's a weekend night,

621
00:38:49,862 --> 00:38:52,840
so we'd have to go to the ER.

622
00:38:52,840 --> 00:38:54,864
You really pinch every penny, don't you?

623
00:38:54,864 --> 00:38:57,638
I respect that, Ms. Hyun Jin.

624
00:38:57,638 --> 00:38:59,738
Hey, Sun Tae Hyung.

625
00:38:59,738 --> 00:39:01,683
We said we'd drop the formalities.

626
00:39:01,683 --> 00:39:04,352
Okay, Woo Hyun Jin.

627
00:39:04,352 --> 00:39:06,325
Woo Hyun Jin.

628
00:39:11,307 --> 00:39:13,808
I got worried when the call dropped.

629
00:39:13,808 --> 00:39:15,767
When I called back, your phone was off.

630
00:39:15,767 --> 00:39:17,394
I'm sorry.

631
00:39:17,394 --> 00:39:18,701
There was...

632
00:39:18,701 --> 00:39:20,832
kind of an incident.

633
00:39:20,832 --> 00:39:22,734
An incident?

634
00:39:26,274 --> 00:39:28,177
Well...

635
00:39:29,721 --> 00:39:31,861
You go inside first.

636
00:39:52,264 --> 00:39:53,864
If her phone was off,

637
00:39:53,864 --> 00:39:55,861
you could've just assumed it was charging.

638
00:39:55,861 --> 00:39:58,529
Why rush all the way to her place?

639
00:39:58,529 --> 00:40:01,382
How romantic.

640
00:40:09,270 --> 00:40:11,143
What?

641
00:40:17,382 --> 00:40:20,047
Yoon Seong, I'm really fine.

642
00:40:20,047 --> 00:40:22,383
You said you rolled down a mountain.

643
00:40:22,383 --> 00:40:25,629
And it was raining.
If it gets infected, that's serious.

644
00:40:33,410 --> 00:40:35,551
[Emergency Medical Center]

645
00:40:45,489 --> 00:40:47,741
What did they say? Are you okay?

646
00:40:47,741 --> 00:40:49,363
Yeah.

647
00:40:49,363 --> 00:40:53,170
They said if I take the antibiotics
and apply the ointment, I'll be fine.

648
00:40:54,331 --> 00:40:55,376
You've taken me

649
00:40:55,376 --> 00:40:58,109
to the ER twice in just a few days.

650
00:40:58,109 --> 00:40:59,503
I know.

651
00:40:59,503 --> 00:41:01,185
Let's keep it at two.

652
00:41:01,185 --> 00:41:03,934
No third time.

653
00:41:03,934 --> 00:41:05,342
Of course.

654
00:41:05,342 --> 00:41:08,509
If you're grateful, let's grab a meal tomorrow.

655
00:41:08,509 --> 00:41:10,681
Sure.

656
00:41:10,681 --> 00:41:13,896
Then I'll treat you to something expensive.

657
00:41:14,560 --> 00:41:16,729
Oh, but

658
00:41:16,729 --> 00:41:19,982
I have Woo Joo on weekends.

659
00:41:19,982 --> 00:41:21,650
Perfect.

660
00:41:21,650 --> 00:41:25,142
There's something I need to say
to that kid anyway.

661
00:41:27,077 --> 00:41:29,348
He's tiny but totally sharp.

662
00:41:29,348 --> 00:41:32,244
The way he got pouty
thinking I was taking his toy...

663
00:41:32,244 --> 00:41:33,370
So cute.

664
00:41:33,370 --> 00:41:34,538
Right?

665
00:41:34,538 --> 00:41:36,264
I'm not just saying that
because he's my nephew.

666
00:41:36,264 --> 00:41:37,630
He's seriously adorable.

667
00:41:37,630 --> 00:41:39,735
Want to see pictures?

668
00:41:39,735 --> 00:41:41,646
Look.

669
00:41:41,646 --> 00:41:43,257
Isn't he the cutest?

670
00:41:43,257 --> 00:41:45,259
So lovely, right?

671
00:41:50,728 --> 00:41:52,982
Why are they taking so long?

672
00:41:54,138 --> 00:41:56,118
Are they dating?

673
00:41:57,334 --> 00:41:58,424
Well...

674
00:41:58,424 --> 00:42:00,857
What's it to me?

675
00:42:02,464 --> 00:42:04,358
I don't know.

676
00:42:18,374 --> 00:42:20,209
He cleaned the whole place himself.

677
00:42:20,209 --> 00:42:22,274
Must've been tough.

678
00:42:29,802 --> 00:42:31,428
I respect that, Ms. Hyun Jin.

679
00:42:31,428 --> 00:42:32,948
We said we'd drop the formalities.

680
00:42:32,948 --> 00:42:35,542
Okay, Woo Hyun Jin.

681
00:42:41,794 --> 00:42:44,175
Looks like they got close pretty fast.

682
00:43:27,067 --> 00:43:28,910
Look over here.

683
00:43:34,241 --> 00:43:36,334
Where are you going?

684
00:43:37,217 --> 00:43:39,936
You've been busy since this morning.

685
00:43:42,499 --> 00:43:46,136
I have a lunch meeting.

686
00:43:49,969 --> 00:43:52,028
With who?

687
00:43:52,618 --> 00:43:54,431
Yoon Seong.

688
00:43:54,431 --> 00:43:57,723
He covered the ER bill yesterday,

689
00:43:57,723 --> 00:43:59,099
and the restaurant we're going to

690
00:43:59,099 --> 00:44:01,937
actually ties into a proposal I'm working on.

691
00:44:01,937 --> 00:44:04,037
So it kind of works out.

692
00:44:07,024 --> 00:44:10,282
Then why are you taking the baby?

693
00:44:10,282 --> 00:44:12,703
It's the weekend. It's my day with Woo Joo.

694
00:44:12,703 --> 00:44:15,047
So I thought I'd take him out.

695
00:44:22,206 --> 00:44:24,886
Go. He's probably waiting.

696
00:44:27,742 --> 00:44:29,682
Did you catch a cold?

697
00:44:29,682 --> 00:44:32,442
My throat's just scratchy. I just woke up.

698
00:44:33,592 --> 00:44:36,115
Oh no.

699
00:44:36,115 --> 00:44:39,508
It's probably from getting soaked yesterday.

700
00:44:40,849 --> 00:44:43,352
- Shouldn't you go to the hospital?
- I'm fine.

701
00:44:43,352 --> 00:44:45,284
Just go.

702
00:44:49,900 --> 00:44:52,236
There's cold medicine in the first aid kit.

703
00:44:52,236 --> 00:44:55,313
- It's...
- I know where it is.

704
00:44:56,026 --> 00:44:57,973
Oh.

705
00:44:57,973 --> 00:45:00,123
Should I pick up cough syrup
and some herbal tonic on the way back?

706
00:45:00,123 --> 00:45:01,416
I said I'm fine.

707
00:45:01,416 --> 00:45:04,466
Just go. Are you leaving or not?

708
00:45:04,466 --> 00:45:06,378
Hey, kid.

709
00:45:07,918 --> 00:45:10,553
Okay, I'm going.

710
00:45:12,297 --> 00:45:14,270
Let's go.

711
00:45:16,427 --> 00:45:18,509
I'm going.

712
00:45:18,509 --> 00:45:20,356
Come on.

713
00:45:28,578 --> 00:45:31,403
I'll just have lunch and won't be late.

714
00:45:31,403 --> 00:45:32,651
If you feel worse, call me.

715
00:45:32,651 --> 00:45:34,445
I'll come right back.

716
00:45:34,445 --> 00:45:36,518
Okay?

717
00:45:46,874 --> 00:45:48,584
Let's go.

718
00:45:48,584 --> 00:45:50,534
Come on.

719
00:45:57,212 --> 00:45:59,011
You didn't have to come pick us up.

720
00:45:59,011 --> 00:46:00,993
How's your leg?

721
00:46:00,993 --> 00:46:04,141
It's a little better today.

722
00:46:04,141 --> 00:46:06,628
I've got something for you.

723
00:46:06,628 --> 00:46:08,528
For me?

724
00:46:14,443 --> 00:46:17,946
Sorry. Not for you.

725
00:46:17,946 --> 00:46:19,512
Hi there.

726
00:46:19,512 --> 00:46:21,038
Let's have fun today.

727
00:46:21,038 --> 00:46:22,950
Here.

728
00:46:33,504 --> 00:46:34,797
Did you...

729
00:46:34,797 --> 00:46:37,257
buy a car seat?

730
00:46:37,257 --> 00:46:39,783
No, I borrowed it.

731
00:46:41,386 --> 00:46:43,177
How old is Woo Joo?

732
00:46:43,177 --> 00:46:45,494
Twenty-one months.

733
00:46:46,266 --> 00:46:48,633
He doesn't seem shy.

734
00:46:48,633 --> 00:46:50,644
I figured I'd skip the stiff suit

735
00:46:50,644 --> 00:46:53,457
and dress a little more casual today.

736
00:46:53,457 --> 00:46:55,984
Oh, I see.

737
00:46:55,984 --> 00:46:59,905
You look like you did in college.

738
00:46:59,905 --> 00:47:02,647
You were really popular back then.

739
00:47:03,984 --> 00:47:07,137
What's that smile? Like you already knew?

740
00:47:07,137 --> 00:47:08,372
Did you know?

741
00:47:08,372 --> 00:47:11,066
Well, my locker was packed

742
00:47:11,066 --> 00:47:14,152
every Valentine's Day.

743
00:47:14,152 --> 00:47:15,796
Beats me.

744
00:47:15,796 --> 00:47:16,964
Right.

745
00:47:16,964 --> 00:47:18,966
You were always like this.

746
00:47:18,966 --> 00:47:20,843
What, you thought I'd changed

747
00:47:20,843 --> 00:47:22,261
after seven years?

748
00:47:22,261 --> 00:47:23,387
Yes.

749
00:47:23,387 --> 00:47:27,295
I thought you'd turned into
some strict manager.

750
00:47:27,295 --> 00:47:29,489
What's that supposed to mean?

751
00:47:29,489 --> 00:47:30,602
You know,

752
00:47:30,602 --> 00:47:32,387
all mature and responsible.

753
00:47:32,387 --> 00:47:35,367
Like a real team leader.

754
00:47:44,825 --> 00:47:46,201
For the abalone porridge,

755
00:47:46,201 --> 00:47:47,903
please keep it unseasoned for the baby.

756
00:47:47,903 --> 00:47:49,555
As we discussed yesterday,

757
00:47:49,555 --> 00:47:53,681
we'll also prepare seaweed soup
and steamed pumpkin for children.

758
00:47:54,293 --> 00:47:55,417
Did you

759
00:47:55,417 --> 00:47:57,361
make a special reservation

760
00:47:57,361 --> 00:47:58,808
because of me?

761
00:47:58,808 --> 00:48:00,591
Didn't I tell you?

762
00:48:00,591 --> 00:48:03,193
I know the chef here.

763
00:48:03,193 --> 00:48:05,095
When I said I was coming with a baby,

764
00:48:05,095 --> 00:48:07,548
he offered to take care of it.

765
00:48:13,395 --> 00:48:14,693
Try it.

766
00:48:14,693 --> 00:48:17,471
It'll help with the concept direction

767
00:48:17,471 --> 00:48:20,504
and menu planning for your proposal.

768
00:48:23,071 --> 00:48:25,240
What?

769
00:48:25,240 --> 00:48:27,524
Does this still bring back memories?

770
00:48:27,524 --> 00:48:29,453
Of cafeteria days?

771
00:48:29,453 --> 00:48:30,996
Not really.

772
00:48:30,996 --> 00:48:34,249
They didn't serve fish much in the cafeteria.

773
00:48:34,249 --> 00:48:36,179
Didn't they?

774
00:48:43,011 --> 00:48:44,068
Is it good?

775
00:48:45,630 --> 00:48:47,503
That's a relief.

776
00:48:58,315 --> 00:49:00,199
Thank you.

777
00:49:15,165 --> 00:49:17,175
- Good?
- Yeah.

778
00:49:18,072 --> 00:49:20,165
You're eating so well.

779
00:49:26,093 --> 00:49:29,187
I don't know. It feels a little strange.

780
00:49:30,514 --> 00:49:33,141
Seven years really is a long time.

781
00:49:33,141 --> 00:49:35,555
You said you're the same, but...

782
00:49:35,555 --> 00:49:39,631
I feel like there's so much about you
I didn't know.

783
00:49:39,631 --> 00:49:42,132
It feels a little unfamiliar.

784
00:49:42,132 --> 00:49:44,417
Not in a bad way.

785
00:49:44,417 --> 00:49:47,166
I just want to get close to you again.

786
00:49:47,166 --> 00:49:49,450
Like before.

787
00:49:52,870 --> 00:49:55,006
If you keep looking that awkward,

788
00:49:55,006 --> 00:49:57,487
the team's going to think I yelled at you.

789
00:49:57,487 --> 00:50:00,145
They'll think I'm a strict manager.

790
00:50:01,227 --> 00:50:02,813
Was it that obvious?

791
00:50:04,030 --> 00:50:06,883
You've never been good at hiding
your expressions.

792
00:50:06,883 --> 00:50:09,134
You're even more transparent than the baby.

793
00:50:09,134 --> 00:50:10,947
Right? Woo Joo.

794
00:50:12,649 --> 00:50:14,307
Hey.

795
00:50:14,307 --> 00:50:15,809
He's really smart, isn't he?

796
00:50:15,809 --> 00:50:17,689
He is, right?

797
00:50:17,689 --> 00:50:19,758
I'm telling you, he really is.

798
00:50:19,758 --> 00:50:22,639
I'm smart.

799
00:50:22,639 --> 00:50:24,030
Finish what's in your mouth first.

800
00:50:24,030 --> 00:50:26,557
I'm smart.

801
00:50:26,557 --> 00:50:28,490
Good?

802
00:51:08,570 --> 00:51:10,783
What's taking so long?

803
00:51:16,720 --> 00:51:19,456
Uncle, this is Bom.

804
00:51:19,456 --> 00:51:23,896
I'm sending you the family photos
from yesterday.

805
00:51:38,266 --> 00:51:40,644
But the lens doesn't lie.

806
00:51:40,644 --> 00:51:42,317
The way you look at someone.

807
00:51:42,317 --> 00:51:44,251
The heart you put into the shot.

808
00:51:44,251 --> 00:51:46,998
You don't get moments like that
without affection.

809
00:51:46,998 --> 00:51:49,942
In the end, the camera reflects your heart.

810
00:52:15,257 --> 00:52:17,396
I'll come get you.

811
00:52:18,223 --> 00:52:21,275
Sometimes I'll come meet you.

812
00:52:21,935 --> 00:52:23,834
So if there's a day

813
00:52:23,834 --> 00:52:27,542
when you're stuck in the rain
without an umbrella,

814
00:52:27,542 --> 00:52:29,635
just call me.

815
00:52:30,448 --> 00:52:33,913
I'll be your umbrella.

816
00:53:01,816 --> 00:53:06,570
[Temporary Housing]

817
00:53:17,029 --> 00:53:19,391
Just a moment.

818
00:53:19,391 --> 00:53:21,926
The person you're calling is not answering...

819
00:53:21,926 --> 00:53:23,497
[Temporary Helper]

820
00:53:23,497 --> 00:53:25,628
Why isn't he picking up?

821
00:53:25,628 --> 00:53:28,973
[Have you eaten something?
Shall I get you something? ]

822
00:53:33,886 --> 00:53:38,506
[Great dessert cafes to visit with a baby]

823
00:53:46,217 --> 00:53:47,567
He really looks like you.

824
00:53:47,567 --> 00:53:49,581
Those big round eyes.

825
00:53:49,581 --> 00:53:52,215
Were you this cute as a kid?

826
00:53:52,215 --> 00:53:53,276
Come on.

827
00:53:53,276 --> 00:53:55,876
Who wasn't cute as a baby?

828
00:53:57,206 --> 00:53:58,482
I was pretty handsome,

829
00:53:58,482 --> 00:54:00,919
even back then.

830
00:54:03,078 --> 00:54:05,209
But being here today,

831
00:54:05,209 --> 00:54:06,898
I think I'm starting to see

832
00:54:06,898 --> 00:54:09,709
how to connect the concept direction
with the story.

833
00:54:09,709 --> 00:54:12,146
If you need to,
check out our past campaign cases.

834
00:54:13,286 --> 00:54:14,798
This quarter's lineup,

835
00:54:14,798 --> 00:54:18,385
dessert's going to be the key element
that sets the whole branding mood.

836
00:54:18,385 --> 00:54:21,859
There's a great dessert cafe nearby.

837
00:54:21,859 --> 00:54:23,965
Want to stop by?

838
00:54:26,810 --> 00:54:28,394
Why?

839
00:54:28,394 --> 00:54:30,543
You don't want to?

840
00:54:31,898 --> 00:54:34,058
Is something wrong?

841
00:54:36,265 --> 00:54:38,071
It's just...

842
00:54:38,071 --> 00:54:40,691
My in-law didn't look well earlier.

843
00:54:40,691 --> 00:54:42,724
I'm worried about him.

844
00:54:55,718 --> 00:54:58,800
Tae Hyung must've been sick last night.

845
00:54:58,800 --> 00:55:02,433
He didn't say anything.
He probably just toughed it out.

846
00:55:02,433 --> 00:55:05,393
It's the rain.

847
00:55:05,393 --> 00:55:06,711
He always gets sick

848
00:55:06,711 --> 00:55:09,555
when it rains.

849
00:55:09,555 --> 00:55:11,515
Maybe it's because no matter how long he waits,

850
00:55:11,515 --> 00:55:14,881
the person he's waiting for never shows up.

851
00:55:14,881 --> 00:55:18,061
And he's left feeling alone.

852
00:56:30,382 --> 00:56:32,721
Are you okay?

853
00:56:33,591 --> 00:56:37,417
Your fever went up to
39 degrees Celsius overnight.

854
00:56:46,074 --> 00:56:50,140
I was this close to calling an ambulance.

855
00:56:54,999 --> 00:56:56,501
Still sick?

856
00:56:56,501 --> 00:56:59,286
Do you want to go to the hospital?

857
00:57:04,083 --> 00:57:06,781
Why were you so late?

858
00:57:10,767 --> 00:57:13,023
You know I hate

859
00:57:13,023 --> 00:57:15,396
waiting for someone.

860
00:57:19,149 --> 00:57:21,262
Sun Tae Hyung...

861
00:57:23,533 --> 00:57:25,663
I like you.

862
00:57:29,507 --> 00:57:31,787
Woo Hyun Jin.

863
00:57:38,456 --> 00:57:41,829
That's why I keep finding myself
waiting for you.

864
00:58:44,739 --> 00:58:46,337
Oh my God, what is this?

865
00:58:46,337 --> 00:58:48,327
Why are you two moving so fast?

866
00:58:48,327 --> 00:58:50,304
This is way more awkward than I expected.

867
00:58:50,304 --> 00:58:51,730
Did something go on between you two?

868
00:58:51,730 --> 00:58:55,597
No, it is not like that at all.

869
00:58:55,597 --> 00:58:57,193
Honestly, I was worried about you.

870
00:58:57,193 --> 00:58:59,208
Living with a guy like that.

871
00:58:59,208 --> 00:59:00,479
Oh, it is Lobby Guy!

872
00:59:00,479 --> 00:59:01,846
The lobby nuisance guy!

873
00:59:01,846 --> 00:59:03,327
Why? What happened?

874
00:59:03,327 --> 00:59:05,984
Woo Joo, have fun with your friends.

875
00:59:05,984 --> 00:59:07,102
I will come get you.

876
00:59:07,102 --> 00:59:10,301
They say some suspicious guy in a hat
has been hanging around at night.

877
00:59:10,301 --> 00:59:12,301
Woo Hyun Jin.
